best in my view.} (7... Nxd5 8. Nxd5 exd5 {is another decent continuation.}) 8.
Qxd4 (8. Nxd4 Nxd5 9. Bb2 Nxc3 10. Bxc3 e5 11. Nf3 Qc7 $132 {[%cal Gf8d8,Gb8c6]
Bxe5 is strongly met with ...Bb4+.}) 8... exd5 (8... Qa5 $5 9. Bd2 exd5 10. Qd3
Nc6 11. Be2 Rd8 12. O-O Ne4 $132) 9. Bb2 (9. Be2 $2 {is already a mistake due
to} Nc6 10. Qd3 Ne4 $1 {when White is on the verge of losing.} 11. Nxd5 (11.
