12... Qa5+ 13. Kf1 Ng3+ 14. hxg3 Bxd3 15. Bxd3 g6 $17) 9... Nc6 10. Qd1 (10.
Qd3 Nb4 11. Qd2 Bg4 $132 {Black has a great game and went on to win in 0-1 (24)
Schlosser,P (2586)-Navara,D (2708)/Saint-Quentin FRA 2014/The Week in Chess
1021 (24).}) 10... Bb4 (10... d4 {also offers a lot of counterplay after} 11.
