1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 Be7 5. g3 {With this, we transpose to a
special line of the Catalan opening with White's knight on c3 and Black's
bishop on e7.} O-O 6. Bg2 Nbd7 $5 {This is the simplest continuation for Black
in my opinion. We keep the option to play ...dxc4, ...while also getting ready
to develop with ...b6, ...Bb7, etc.} ({The main move is} 6... dxc4 {, when
after} 7. Ne5 {Black can play to equalise with} c5 ({or go for the more
complicated} 7... Qd6 8. Nxc4 Qa6)) ({Another big theoretical line begins with
} 6... c6) 7. Qd3 {is White's main move, protecting the c4-pawn.} (7. b3 dxc4 {
Taking on c4, followed by ...c5 is the most straightforward way to equalise.} (
7... b6 {is also not bad at all.} 8. Bb2 Bb7 9. O-O c5) 8. bxc4 c5 9. e3 (9. d5
$6 {is bad due to} Nb6 $15) (9. O-O {poses no problems:} cxd4 10. Qxd4 (10.
Nxd4 Ne5 $132) 10... Nb6 $1 11. Qf4 $11 Nh5 $5 {Chasing the queen is simplest
in my opinion.} (11... Bd7) 12. Qe5 Nf6 13. Rd1 (13. Qf4 $11) 13... Bd7 14. Qf4
Nh5 15. Qe3 Rc8 (15... Nxc4 16. Qd3) 16. Ne5 Nxc4 17. Nxc4 Rxc4 18. Qd3 Rc7 19.
Bf3 Nf6 20. Bf4 Rc5 21. Be3 (21. Ne4 Ra5) 21... Ra5 22. Bxb7 Qc7 $11) 9... cxd4
$5 {Again going for the most concrete line.} ({Keeping the tension with} 9...
Qc7 {is another possibility.} 10. Qe2 b6 11. O-O Bb7 $11) 10. exd4 e5 $1 {
This is the point!} 11. dxe5 (11. O-O exd4 12. Nxd4 Nb6 13. Qd3 Re8 $11) 11...
Qa5 12. exf6 Bxf6 13. Bd2 Bxc3 14. O-O Bxd2 15. Qxd2 Qxd2 16. Nxd2 Rb8 17. Ne4
b6 $11) (7. O-O {With 7.0-0 White sacrifices the c4-pawn - we should
definitely know what to do after this!} dxc4 $1 {We accept the challenge.} 8.
a4 (8. Nd2 {is harmless.} Nb6 9. e3 c5 10. dxc5 Bxc5 $11 {Black is at least
equal.}) (8. e4 {is met strongly with} b5 $1 9. Nxb5 (9. d5 $2 b4 10. dxe6 fxe6
$17) (9. Qe2 c6 10. Rd1 Bb7 $15) (9. e5 Nd5 10. Nxb5 {transposes.}) 9... Bb7 ({
Not} 9... Nxe4 $6 10. Nd2 {[%cal Gg2a8]}) 10. e5 ({White achieves nothing with
} 10. Bf4 Nxe4 11. Bxc7 Qc8 12. Bf4 Ndf6 $132) 10... Nd5 11. Nd2 (11. Qe2 {
is similar.} Rb8 12. Nc3 c5 $132) 11... Rb8 12. a4 (12. Nxc4 Ba6 13. a4 c6 14.
