{[#] Black to move How did Black manage to gain a positional advantage?} 13...
a5 $1 $15 {[%cal Ga5a4] Black can attack White's structure on the queenside.
Black gets the advantage because White fails to create counterplay.} ({The
game continued with} 13... a5 14. e3 a4 15. Qc2 a3 16. Bc3 Nf6 17. Ne5 Ne4 18.
Rac1 Qe7 $15 {½-½ (37) Prohaszka,P (2573)-Cheparinov,I (2672) Terme Catez
2022. Black is much better. The a3-pawn is powerful, and he will continue with
...f6 and possibly ...h5-h4. White has no play whatsoever. (see Lesson 7)}) *

